      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "**MEMORANDUM**\n\nTo: All Department Heads  \nFrom: [Your Name], Compliance Officer  \nDate: [Today's Date]  \nSubject: New Onboarding Process KYC Compliance\n\nDear Team,\n\nAs part of our commitment to maintaining the highest standards of regulatory compliance, we are implementing a new onboarding process that strictly adheres to Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations. This memo outlines the essential steps and legal terminology required to ensure full compliance with our internal and external regulatory requirements.\n\n1. **Customer Identification Program (CIP):** We will verify the identity of all new customers through government-issued identification, such as a driver's license or passport, and additional documentation as necessary.\n\n2. **Customer Due Diligence (CDD):** We will conduct enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers, including obtaining information on the source of funds, the purpose of the account, and any potential links to criminal activity.\n\n3. **Risk Assessment:** A thorough risk assessment will be conducted for each new customer, considering factors such as geographic location, transaction patterns, and industry sector.\n\n4. **Sanctions Screening:** We will screen all new customers against global sanctions lists, including OFAC, EU Sanctions, and UN Sanctions, to ensure no involvement",
      "source": "target",
